<br>
Well we had a good run yesterday and I wanted to start this thread to post what we learned in the new Hate so we can discuss it and be better prepaired for the next trip.<br>
<br>
1. We need to start early. Starting at 11 am est does not work for us at all on the weekends. We have gotten beaten to the plane 2 out of 3 times and as we now know a broken hate is a mediocre raid at best drop wise.<br>
<br>
2. The imps in the SW corner are wussy and don't tend to move from the SW corner. You can run through them, kill them and then move away with noaggro from the next batch that pop. Also meaning the SW camp is still viable if you can get to it.<br>
<br>
3. The Aggro range on 50 plus is small all things considered. We did well with not aggroing to much and only getting the occasional add.<br>
<br>
4. The 1st floor boss mobs albeit a bit tougher then your standard hate mob I think they were level 56 or 57 seem to consistently drop and maybe even 2 pieces of class armor.<br>
<br>
5. Sobek is not liked in Hate. For some reason he was marked for death by the 2nd floor and got HT's frequently. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  We need to figure this one out cause I don't think it had to do with wall aggro, maybe a song he was playing not sure.<br>
<br>
6. Stay off the walls when fighting.<br>
<br>
7. 4 groups of 50 plus can easily kill the mobs on the 1st floor.<br>
<br>
8. Rouge's are a must for hate. Once Diadem was there the pulls were alot more percise and we pulled much faster.<br>
<br>
We camped the Zone in first as we got our mess together which went well. We then moved to the SW corner which also worked well. Then we moved to the Maestro house / throne room. All of these spots worked well for us as camps even though we didn't have a full pop zone wise.<br>
<br>
Things I think people weren't aware of:<br>
<br>
Rats and Liches are not static pops but 30 min spawn time roamers. Hence the large amount of rats killed.<br>
<br>
Revenants are static spawns, we got these cause the previous guild hadn't pulled them.<br>
<br>
Hate is by no means like Fear. All though the mobs are the same level and drop class loot like fear the similarity ends there. The nature of the house's static spawns and the small streets makes hate more deadly in some respects. You can never really tell what your going to aggro when you walk through hate due to that and the patrols. CR in hate is horrible compared to fear. You can't just zone in and once there you have all the previously mentioned to contend with while CR'n.<br>
<br>
All in all a good raid given the circumstances. Please post anything that I missed so that we can keep a list of things to be aware of for those going to hate.<br>
<br>
Zen <p>Zenknight Darkhorse,
53 Champion,
Warlord ,
Screaming Fist</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukrytogspiritwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krytog Spiritwalker</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/30/01 9:47:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=176.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lessons from Hate</span><hr size=1> Only 2 things of note from my side. If you are planning on going on a raid plan to be there, NOT just get up there then go log for a couple hours and come back later. You force the entire raid party to have to wait while they a) have to get you, b) CR you  c) worry with you training into the main camp.<br>
<br>
Cash Loots - I listened to a fair amount of bickering both ooc and in my group.  The hate stones are about 250pp and the chanters and cleric burn some some serious plat on a 8 hour raid keeping the buffs up also. THAT is way those individuals get dibs on the cash loots. Anything that exceeds the costs for those individuals will get rolled on as Zenknight let us roll.<br>
<br>
Xp - Raids tend to be xp poor for the most part. There were complaints that the groups were rigged for xp.  We had a cleric shortage and therefore the tanks get put into groups with a cleric that could HEAL them. On a raid we are there to kill the mobs in the most efficient manner possible. If groups can be balanced then they will be, but the raid leader has to assess how to ensure success with the least amount of risk. We get wiped nobody gets anything but a really boring day.<br>
<br>
