Ask of the Spirits and the way will be shown...</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uzenknight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zenknight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/30/01 10:20:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=176.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lessons from Hate</span><hr size=1> Wow <br>
<br>
<br>
I didn't realize we were getting complaints like that accept for the loot.<br>
<br>
Ok for the record PLANES RAIDS ARE NOT MEANT FOR EXP THEY ARE MEANT FOR LOOT!!!<br>
<br>
Typical group make up in Hate at least works like this.<br>
<br>
Typical Pull group<br>
<br>
Monk FD puller Sk's can be used but monk's are usualy better<br>
Rouge Scout<br>
War Tagger Taunter<br>
Clr Enuff said<br>
Enc Mez<br>
Wiz Porter and big damage<br>
<br>
Typically High HP tanks are grouped with the clerics due to the ability to taunt mobs off of casters. Enchanters are the same group with the clerics so they live longer then 3 seconds when a mez is broken.<br>
<br>
So the groups were designed for survivability not xp the pull group was heavy with damage dealers and we did get the most exp of the night.<br>
<br>
On a fear raid you can do a number of things differently group wise for exp balance, it's an outside zone with plenty of room to pull and fight with little aggro. Hate is not. Hate is an inside zone a town to be exact and with a full pop you can aggro a ton of stuff while fighting, the groups were designed to kill fast which is a neccessity when it get's ugly. If you don't believe me ask the enchanters cause they are all Hate veterans and I doubt they would disagree.<br>
<br>
I know that it seems as if we can all just go on a planes raid and should be able to get exp. Like I have said a few times now Hate is not Fear, Hate can be much worse then Fear due to building aggro and the greater chance of a very long expensive CR. You can't fear, snare, root or use pets really and every where you fight is a confined space.<br>
<br>
We as an organization need to get a handle on our expectations for these raids. If you go expecting loot or exp then your out of luck. Sometimes the loot falls and sometimes it doesn't and EXP on a large scale raid is usually dominated by one or 2 groups. I know some people that have done 100 or so hate runs and still haven't gotten all of their class armor. You can't go expecting to get anything especially with 5 other of your class there. Treat loot and exp as a bonus to going and when you do get a piece of class armor or loot it will make all worth while.<br>
<br>
Zen <p>Zenknight Darkhorse,
53 Champion,
Warlord ,
Screaming Fist</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utelivaksk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TelivakSK</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/30/01 10:52:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=176.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lessons from Hate</span><hr size=1> I told Zenknight before we ported up that I needed to log for an hour to get some things done and if I should bother going since that was the case.  He said yes, so I went.  I wouldn't have bothered going otherwise.  I'm sorry if you feel that is inappropriate but for me at least, I take my RL in consideration when I play EQ. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uzenknight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zenknight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/30/01 10:56:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=176.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lessons from Hate</span><hr size=1> Krytog<br>
