53 Champion,
Warlord ,
Screaming Fist</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukrytogspiritwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krytog Spiritwalker</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/30/01 11:18:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=176.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lessons from Hate</span><hr size=1> When I make comments on the open forum I usually will make general statements not to target specific people, but hopefully for useful feedback as a whole. At no point did I actually name you telivak.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     I fully understand RL considerations.  Your leaving in itself was no biggie. However, once that door is open ppl can say well they don't mind if I play for a couple hours, log out, and join back in a bit. How well will it play out if we had several ppl doing this across the course of a raid? What if the zone had repopped while you were gone? The planes have a lot of variables that are hard to predict and having ppl coming and going is not good, IMHO. However, there are always exceptions. We just need to make the ppl understand they are the exception and not the rule. The only point is not to jeopardize the rest of the raid unneccesarily under any circumstance.<br>
<br>
My comments are geared to providing the most cohesive, effective, and fun raid as possible, as i see it. If I have issue with a specific person they will know it. <br>
<br>
