Ask of the Spirits and the way will be shown...</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukrytogspiritwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krytog Spiritwalker</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0> at: 4/30/01 11:28:59 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utelivaksk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TelivakSK</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/30/01 11:31:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=176.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lessons from Hate</span><hr size=1> Don't get all defensive now, that wasn't meant as a snide comment.  It's what I do when I play EQ.  Some people I know play EQ thru all the distractions in the RL, that's no exaggeration but that's not what I do.  Everyone who has played with me or known me long enough, KNOWS that I will decline invites or raids if I have something I need to finish in RL or otherwise busy with something in game.  This was slightly different because I had promised Zenknight on attending the raid and something came up in RL that I needed to take care of.  I thought you meant me when you made that logging for a few hours comment because I was the only one, that I knew of, who had to log upon porting in.  Not a unreasonable assumption under the circumstances.<br>
<br>
P.S: I fully understand the implications involved logging for a few in the middle of a big raid and no, I didn't think of the possible future implications when it comes people wanting to log in the middle of a raid.  I've been to more than my share of long, large scale raids.  That was why I asked Zenknight if I should go or not due to the circumstances in the first place.  I just don't want something like this to come back and bite me in the ass or in your arguement, people using it as an excuse of &quot;if he did it, so can I&quot;, since I did clear it with the raid leader and it was okayed. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utelivaksk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TelivakSK</A> at: 4/30/01 11:53:43 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubamilbanebringer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bamil Banebringer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/30/01 12:24:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=176.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lessons from Hate</span><hr size=1> Alright, I'm bigger than both of you so I suggest you break it up. It would be more than embarassing for me to school you both again in the Arena.... let's see you root or fear when I'm hasting you for a dirt nap.<br>
<br>
As for Hate, I think it went well. We have plenty of room for improvement, but this is a huge step from our last Hate run, (gigantic understatement).<br>
<br>
We need to keep the OOC'ing to a minimum, it was very distracting at times. Let the pull team decide what to pull. We also should set a definitive time when we say we are going to quit. This will allow people to plan for things in RL or ingame, as well as provide us a timeframe for which we would need to request reinforcements for any willing to stay.<br>
<br>
Overall I think we did a great job, only the occasional death and some decent loot/cash drops. Let's continue to improve.<br>
<br>
-BamBam<br>
52 Champion<br>
Spirit Guardians <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukoschnathrak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kosch Nathrak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/30/01 2:40:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=176.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lessons from Hate</span><hr size=1> Just like to thank everyone for a fun hate raid on sunday. I really did enjoy myself. Its good to see that we are all pulling together and turning into a planes capable group. I think like Bamil said it was a major improvment over the last one hehe 2 hour CR for me, but experiance comes through death, learning and figuring out why you always put your socks on inside out.<br>
