&quot;lighting a match is a skill, Burning a village is an art form&quot;  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umyriahwind.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Myriahwind</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/30/01 3:16:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=176.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lessons from Hate</span><hr size=1> Ok, some stuff I learned or was reminded of.<br>
<br>
1. AOEs are the way to death or adds. Chanters should not use AOE stuns and I believe a certain bard got in trouble with AOE offensive spells.<br>
<br>
2. Hotkey targets. What do you say? The way I can cast clarity two on 15 to 20 different people is that I have a hotkey for each person who requests clarity. For example I have a hotkey with title &quot;Holt&quot; and have &quot;/tar holt&quot; in the body of the hotkey. That way I can select anyone I want in the raid. Healers might consider doing this same thing to heal each other even those in separate groups. Maybe the healers from two groups could aggree to back up each other in this manner. (I apologize if all the healers are already doing this. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
<br>
3. Chanters should hotkey assist for each other. Then when a mob aggros on one chanter the others can use hotkey to select that mob to mez. We also should have a hotkey with a tell to another chanter &quot;assist me please and mezz this sucker that is kicking my butt&quot;<br>
<br>
4. OCC comments should be kept to a minimum. I know it is boring and I also use OOC tooooo much. But we need to stop all the extra spam.<br>
<br>
5. Adds need to be shouted out. It is very hard for chanters to see what is happening. So tell us about extra mobs so we can mez them.<br>
<br>
6. The minor bosses can not be effectively mezzed so we should kill those first if we got more than one mob in the pull.<br>
<br>
7. DOTs is something we should talk about. I stopped using them because if we need to switch targets the chanter trying to mez the old target (that has been DOTed) gets eatten alive. Also there is a little trouble with dispelling mobs and DOTs.<br>
<br>
8. The raid leader obviously has the authority to let someone log and come back. Telivak and Krytog covered all the important points about this above.<br>
<br>
9. Reality Check.  The planes are not about exp, or cash loot. They are about planes equipment (uber loot), planes gems, and working together as a team. The chance of getting some uber loot is about one-in-five. So every fifth planes raid or so you should get something. Some people get more than this; some less. When we get higher level and can do second floor in Hate mobs, the chance of getting loot will improve.<br>
<br>
10. Whining about experience, cash, or what mobs are pulled is really not helpful. If you have some knowledge that would be useful to the pull team, meantion it to the raid leader. If you think the puller might have missed two mobs that hide in a certain corner, please tell that to the raid leader. Remember you should not expect to get anything on 4 out of five raids.<br>
<br>
Myriah<br>
